PARAGRAPH.#text: Oneok Inc.'s OKE third-quarter earnings fell roughly 4% on charges related to the winding down of the company's energy-services segment. The pipeline and natural-gas gathering business, Oneok Partners LP OKS, saw its third-quarter profit tumble 6.9% as higher natural-gas volumes gathered and processed were offset by impacts from lower realized prices for natural gas and natural-gas liquids, as well as sharply narrower NGL price differentials. For the year, Oneok Partners lowered  the upper end of its earnings estimate by $40 million and now expects $790 million to $830 million.

Pipeline and natural-gas gathering business Oneok Partners LP OKS  reported that its second-quarter profit increased 2% amid narrower natural-gas-liquids price spreads and continued ethane-rejection related impacts. Oneok, which distributes natural gas through utilities in Oklahoma, Kansas and Texas, has faced challenges resulting from low natural-gas prices caused by an overabundance of supply.

Headlines.Author: Barbara Kollmeyer
Headlines.Headline: U.S. Stock Futures Down Sharply, But Up From Earlier Lows

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Barbara Kollmeyer and Sara Sjolin Futures for the Dow Jones Industrial Average tumbled 169 points, or 1.3%, to 13,098, while those for the Standard & Poor's 500 index erased 22.25 points, or 1.4%, to 1,420.25. Futures for the Nasdaq-100 index slid 39.50 points, or 1.5%, to 2,650.50. After a closed-door meeting on Thursday evening, Republicans said they didn't have the votes needed to back up the tax-cut bill, which would have, among other measures, extended tax cuts on incomes below $1 million.

Headlines.Author: Mia Lamar
Headlines.Headline: Oneok 3rd-Quarter Profit Up 8.1% on Improved Volumes

PARAGRAPH.#text: Oneok Inc.'s OKE third-quarter earnings rose 8.1% on strength at its Oneok Partners LP OKS unit. Weakened natural gas prices amid a glut of supply have been a challenge for Oneok, which distributes natural gas through utilities in Oklahoma, Kansas and Texas. John W. Gibson, Oneok's chief executive, attributed the performance of Oneok Partners to completed growth projects that provided increased natural gas volumes. The energy services segment, however, "continues to face a challenging market environment," he said.

Headlines.Author: Nathalie Tadena
Headlines.Headline: Oneok 2nd-Quarter Profit Up 18%; Oneok Partners Net Jumps 21%

PARAGRAPH.#text: Oneok Inc.'s OKE second-quarter profit rose 18%, helped by strong results from its Oneok Partners LP OKS unit, which saw earnings improve 21%. Oneok lowered its full-year net-income guidance to a range of $345 million to $375 million, down from its prior view of $360 million to $410 million. Oneok pointed to lower expected earnings in the energy-services and natural-gas distribution segments, offset partially by higher expected earnings in Oneok Partners. Oneok Partners raised its 2012 net-income guidance to a range of $860 million to $910 million, up from its prior view of $810 million to $870 million.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Oneok 2nd-Quarter Profit Up 18%; Oneok Partners Net Jumps 21%

Headlines.Author: CBS.MarketWatch.com
Headlines.Headline: Top Ten: Best stories, commentary -- March 13-19

PARAGRAPH.#text:
LONDON (CBS.MW) -- Punch drunk. That's what Europeans think of the U.S. investors
    who sent the  briefly through 10,000. Much of the Dow's good fortune has been
    bound up with one of America's favorite pastimes -- getting rich by investing in the stock
    markets. This grates on Europe's nerves. In Europe, personal dabbling in the markets is,
    by comparison, almost unheard of. And it's this American proclivity that makes European
    investors particularly nervous. Unlike the New York Stock Exchange trading floor, where
    the Magical Moment was met with cheers, traders on the floors of European bourses watched
    with apprehension. "There's the danger that there's a behavioral impact at reaching
    10,000," as one London-based economist put it.

Headlines.BodyHeadline: Top Ten: Best stories, commentary -- March 13-19
